  "prompt": "Is it allowed to watch ISRO satellite launch from safe distance at Sriharikota?",
  "response": "Generally, ISRO (Indian Space Research Organisation) allows limited public viewing of satellite launches from their Satish Dhawan Space Centre at Sriharikota, but with certain restrictions:\n\n1. Permission is required: You cannot simply walk in on launch day.\n\n2. Prior registration: Interested viewers need to register in advance through ISRO's official website or designated channels.\n\n3. Limited seats: Only a limited number of passes are issued for public viewing.\n\n4. Specific viewing area: Spectators are allowed only in designated safe viewing zones.\n\n5. Security checks: Strict security protocols are followed.\n\n6. Advance notice: Viewing opportunities are announced before each launch.\n\nKey recommendations:\n- Check ISRO's official website for launch schedules and viewing details\n- Register early\n- Follow all instructions provided by authorities\n- Carry necessary identification\n- Arrive well in advance of the launch time\n\nIt's best to visit ISRO's official website or contact them directly for the most current information about public viewing opportunities for specific launches.",
